cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a novel warp for natural image stitching, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves image processing and graphics, which are related to cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of homography and cylindrical warps suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
